{"success":true,"serverVersion":12,"dataset":[{"id":9727,"version":1,"subVersion":7,"packageVersion":"3.6.2","serverVersion":12,"lang":"en","new_changes":true,"published":true,"enableTutorialMode":true,"webPushEnabled":true,"wearablesEnabled":true,"wearablesProviders":["withings","oura"],"wearablesDataTypes":[],"accessKeys":["ssrc"],"langCodes":["en"],"title":"Surrey Sleep & Daily Experiences Study","studyDescription":"<p>Thank you for taking part in our research. Over <strong>three consecutive days</strong> we will ask you to complete a few short questionnaires on your phone:</p><ul><li>☀️ <strong>Morning</strong> — a brief sleep diary about the night before</li><li>📋 <strong>Daytime</strong> — two quick momentary check-ins on how you are feeling</li><li>🌙 <strong>Evening</strong> — a short reflection on your day</li></ul><p>Each questionnaire takes about <strong>4–5 minutes</strong>, and we will send a notification when each one is ready.</p>","informedConsentForm":"Surrey Sleep & Daily Experiences Study — Informed Consent\n\nPlease read this information carefully before deciding whether to take part.\n\nPURPOSE\nThis study looks at day-to-day patterns in sleep, mood and daily experiences, and how they change across a typical few days.\n\nWHAT TAKING PART INVOLVES\n• The study runs for 3 days, beginning the day after you sign up.\n• Each day you will receive 4 short questionnaires: one in the morning (sleep diary), two during the day (momentary check-ins) and one in the evening (reflection).\n• Each questionnaire takes about 4–5 minutes, and you will get a notification when it is ready.\n\nVOLUNTARY PARTICIPATION\nTaking part is entirely voluntary. You may skip any question and you can withdraw at any time, without giving a reason and without any disadvantage.\n\nDATA & CONFIDENTIALITY\nYour responses are identified only by a randomly generated ID — we do not collect your name or contact details. Data are stored securely and used for research purposes only, in line with UK GDPR and the University of Surrey's data protection policy.\n\nETHICS\nThis study has been reviewed and approved by the University of Surrey ethics committee [approval reference to be added].\n\nCONTACT\nFor any questions, please contact the research team:\nsleep@surrey.ac.uk · +44 (0)1483 682502\n\nBy tapping \"I consent\" below you confirm that you have read and understood this information, that you are 18 or older, and that you agree to take part.","postInstallInstructions":"What to expect:\n• Morning Questionnaire — a sleep diary, around 8:00 each morning\n• Momentary Check-ins — a few times during the day (around 10:00, 14:00, 18:00)\n• Evening Questionnaire — a short reflection, around 20:00","tutorialOffer":"Before you begin, would you like a quick guided tour? You can try each questionnaire once as a practice run — nothing you enter is saved.","tutorialIntro":"Here's a quick tour of the study. Below are the questionnaires you'll complete each day — ☀️ a morning sleep diary, 📋 daytime momentary check-ins, and 🌙 an evening reflection. Tap \"Practice\" on any one to try it out (nothing you enter is saved). When you're ready, continue to the study.","questionnaires":[{"internalId":29855,"durationPeriodDays":3,"durationStartingAfterDays":1,"virtualInputs":[],"title":"☀️ Morning Questionnaire","actionTriggers":[{"actions":[{"msgText":"Good morning! Please answer the following questions about last night's sleep."}],"schedules":[{"userEditable":false,"signalTimes":[{"startTimeOfDay":28800000,"endTimeOfDay":28800000}]}],"eventTriggers":[]}],"pages":[{"header":"Karolinska Sleep Diary","inputs":[{"responseType":"time","name":"morningBedtime","required":true,"text":"What time did you go to bed last night?","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"time","name":"morningWakeTime","required":true,"text":"What time did you wake up this morning?","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"duration","name":"morningTotalSleep","required":true,"text":"How long do you think you slept in total?","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"duration","name":"morningSleepLatency","required":true,"text":"How long did it take you to fall asleep?","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"likert","name":"morningSleepQuality","required":true,"text":"How did you sleep?","leftSideLabel":"Very poorly","rightSideLabel":"Very well","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"likert","name":"morningFeelingRefreshed","required":true,"text":"How do you feel after waking up?","leftSideLabel":"Not at all refreshed","rightSideLabel":"Completely refreshed","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"likert","name":"morningSleepCalmness","required":true,"text":"How calm was your sleep?","leftSideLabel":"Very restless","rightSideLabel":"Very calm","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"likert","name":"morningSleepContinuity","required":true,"text":"Did you sleep throughout the time allotted?","leftSideLabel":"Not at all","rightSideLabel":"Yes","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"likert","name":"morningEaseWaking","required":true,"text":"How easy was it to wake up?","leftSideLabel":"Very difficult","rightSideLabel":"Very easy","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"likert","name":"morningEaseFallingAsleep","required":true,"text":"How easy was it to fall asleep?","leftSideLabel":"Very difficult","rightSideLabel":"Very easy","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"likert","name":"morningDreaming","required":true,"text":"How much did you dream?","leftSideLabel":"Not at all","rightSideLabel":"A lot","listChoices":[],"subInputs":[]},{"responseType":"list_single","name":"morningNightWakings","required":true,"text":"How many times did you wake up during the night?","listChoices":["0","1","2","3","4","5+"],"subInputs":[]}]},{"header":"Bed Exit Diary","inputs":[{"responseType":"list_single","name":"morningBedExits","required":true,"text":"How many times did you get out of bed